text: Old Fannegusha Creek is a stream in Holmes County the U.S. state of Mississippi. It is a tributary to Tchula Lake. The stream begins at just west of Shackleford and the confluence with Tchula Lake is at .Marcella, MS, 7.5 Minute Topographic Quadrangle, USGS, 1982 Fannegusha is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "tasty squirrel". Variant names for Fannegusha Creek are "Foney Bush Creek", "Funnegusha Creek", and "Funnigusha Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Holmes County, Mississippi
